values:
My car is messing up yet again and I am beginning to wonder what the fuck I spent 800 dollars on a few weeks ago. I am bringing it back to the shop tomorrow and I hope they figure it out. Grrr...
On a lighter note ~ I hung out with a sweet guy tonight and I had a really, really, really great time. He is a cool cat, that's for sure. We went to La Bella Italia for dinner and now that is my all-time favorite restaurant... yum! I actually felt like I was in Europe because the atmosphere was amazing in there. Oh yes, and not to mention that there are all foreigners working there. :) So... I am getting a job there. I have to go back tomorrow after 5 and talk to the lady and I really, really hope she hires me. She said she needs a "bread/buss girl" in about 2 weeks and that would be sweeeeeet because she said they make 6 dollars hourly plus tips!!! And that's bad ass money for just having to bring bread to the table then help clean afterwards! How exciting! Plus, I would get to meet allt he Euros that work in there and make new friends from different countries. Only down side is it is way the hell out on Laskin but who cares - it is most definately worth it! 
After dinner we went back to his place and watched a movie called 'Employee of the Month'... one of the coolest movies everrr. Then I started to get sleepy so I came home. I had a really, really great time hanging with him... he's my new super nice friend. 
When I got home I talked to Alex for over an hour. He seems like a really nice guy and I cannot wait to meet him. Maybe I will meet him tomorrow... or this weekend... we'll see. 
I am exhausted right now... thank God I can sleep in. :)
I hope Jenny had a great time at Ashley... I can't wait to talk to her tomorrow!

Yesterday I sat around the house all day like a fat lazy blob. All day I was debating whether or not to go to the Mae show and I finally decided on going and I am so glad I did. I went to pick up Jenny and we had a blast. We were definately the oldest people there but it's okay because it was really fun. It was funny because while we were standing in line to get our tickets from will call, we were pretty much getting high from the fumes of the dreaded X marker! Hahaha... I don't miss that shit one bit! The first band was putting us to sleep so we went to get some expensive ass NorVa beers. The bartender let us sample Dos Equis and it went down real smooth so that's what I got. It was kind of a cheap version of Corona but still good. So after getting our beer we saw her junior high crush but he was with a girl so Jenny didn't say anything. We looked away for one second and when we looked back he was gone! So we spent the majority of the night looking for him because I told Jenny she HAD to talk to him. We couldn't find him all night... crazyness. Thanks to Jenny, I got to talk to the person I wanted to talk to but the conversation was SO lame. Me: "Hey!" Him: "Hi!" Me: "I like your hair!" Him: "I like yours too!" AKWARD MOMENT OF SILENCE... Me: "Okay, bye." And I walked away. Geez... Since we hadn't seen Ty (her junior high crush) we decided to wait and watch everyone exit and we saw finalyl saw him! He walked by and I thought Jenny wasn't going to say anything so I yelled his name and then so did Jenny... "TY! TY! TY!" He turned around and waved but did not really recognize her and when we walked out he was staring at her. I bet he's still thinking about her today like, "Who's that hot girl that said hi to me?" Hahaha. So we left the NorVa and went to the parking garage and I called my "ex friend with benefits" hahaha. Jenny was laughing sooo hard because of the hot steamy sexual conversation I had with him... Hahaha! It was the funniest shit ever! <3 Then I tried to take her home but I got lost and we ended up almost to Suffolk but it's okay because we had a lot of fun rapping in the car [You can do it put your back into it! I can do it put your ass into it]. We got to her house late and sat in the car wishing we had gone to dance at Time... damn it, we should have. Hehe. When I was coming home I saw B and it was sooo crazy because we were JUST talking about him! He was driving next to me yelling out the window then got behind me and flashed his brights and I didn't know who it was at first so I got kind of scared... then I saw it was him and called Jenny! It was a great night. I didn't go to work today because I wasn't feeling too well. Tonight I'm working for my new job - Williamsburn Vacations. I really hope it's easy and fun. Oh yes, and I found some really cool hot boys that have boyfriend potential. Hehe.

I do not want to be a nurse anymore. My parents are going to be SO mad that I changed my major again and that I dropped my classes for this semester but they are just going to have to deal with it. 
I have great potential to go far in the field of marketing and I would be a complete idiot to not follow that. I am going to apply at ODU for the fall and get student loans to pay for my own classes. I do not have all of my prerequisites to get into the marketing program but I will do those through ODU. The way I see it... TCC sucks away my life and I am not motivated when I take classes there. I need to go to a real school. My goal is set and I will stop at nothing to achieve it.

Although I was not feeling well, I had a lot of fun last night. I hung out with Jared all night. We went to Live to see a show and then we went to EJs until around 2. It was nice seeing Jared, EJ, Kenny, Kayla, Josh, and so many other people. I also met a lot of great people.
My throat still hurts and that is pissing me off. I really want to go to Relative tonight to see Mae and get their cd but I am not feeling too well so we shall see. 
My mom left for Spain today and I am so jealous. I really wish I was on my way to Spain. <3
Speaking of Spain, I talked to Juan for awhile online and we talked about missing Europe. 
I have a job interview tomorrow afternoon for my second job and I am so super excited. I am unsure of what the job is but the hours are great and the guy I talked to sounded so super nice. :)
I talked to a guy online for a good half hour today. He seems like a really great guy. He is super handsome and seems really nice. He also seems to have his head on his shoulders. And did I mention he is super hot? Haha. I think we are going to make plans to hang out this weekend and I am excited. 
I wonder if things are finally going to work out for me? Aah, I cannot look too far ahead and get my hopes up. He is cute though... haha.

I finally know what is missing from my life... God. I have been distancing myself from Him and I have not realized it until now. Maybe this is the reason I am not truly happy. I think the first step for me to get my life in order is to find a church and surround myself with people who follow in God's footsteps. I would like to make new friends and actually "belong" to a group, maybe join a youth group or something. All I know is right now I am wasting my life away with absolutely no purpose to my existance. I need a purpose. I really dislike going to bed each night after an empty day with no accomplishments and no purpose. I would like to go to bed feeling good about myself and proud of the things I did that day. I am going to get the book called 'A Purpose Driven Life' because Dyan said it really helped her find herself and that's what I need to do... I need to find myself.

+i am almost done doing all of my laundry! -i got mad at nathan and now we're not on good terms. -i am still sick! +i haven't eaten much so i probably lost a few pounds. -i've missed 4 days of work. +my room is clean. +i ordered a comforter and sheets! -i'm probably missing work again tomorrow. +nathan and i are going out to lunch and probably going to watch 'the ring'. -'the ring' is going to scare the shit out of me.

Why is marijuana not legal? Why is marijuana not legal? 
It's a natural plant that grows in the dirt. 
Do you know what's not natural?
80 year old dudes with hard-ons. That's not natural.
But we got pills for that.
We're dedicating all our medical resources to keeping the old guys erect,
but we're putting people in jail for something that grows in the dirt?

You know we have more prescription drugs now.
Every commercial that comes on TV is a prescription drug ad.
I can't watch TV for four minutes without thinking I have five serious diseases.
Like: "Do you ever wake up tired in the morning?"
Oh my god I have this, write this down. Whatever it is, I have it. 
Half the time I don't even know what the commercial is:
people running in fields or flying kites or swimming in the ocean.
I'm like that is the greatest disease ever. How do you get that?
That disease comes with a hot chick and a puppy. 

The schools now: It is all about self-esteem in the schools now.
Build the kids' self-esteem, make them feel good about themselves.
If everybody grows up with high self-esteem, who is going to dance in our strip clubs?
What's going to happen to our porno industry?
These women don't just grown on trees. 
It takes lots of drunk dads missing dance recitals before you decide to blow a goat on the internet for fifty bucks.
And if that disappears, where does that leave me on a Friday night with my new high speed connection?

Masterminds are another word that comes up all the time.
You keep hearing about these terrorists masterminds that get killed in the middle east. 
Terrorists masterminds.
Mastermind is sort of a lofty way to describe what these guys do, don't you think?
They're not masterminds.
"OK, you take bomb, right? And you put in your backpack. And you get on bus and you blow yourself up. Alright?"
"Why do I have to blow myself up? Why can't I just:"
"Who's the fucking mastermind here? Me or you?"

Americans, let's face it: We've been a spoiled country for a long time. 
Do you know what the number one health risk in America is? 
Obesity. They say we're in the middle of an obesity epidemic.
An epidemic like it is polio. Like we'll be telling our grand kids about it one day.
The Great Obesity Epidemic of 2004.
"How'd you get through it grandpa?"
"Oh, it was horrible Johnny, there was cheesecake and pork chops everywhere."

Nobody knows why were getting fatter? Look at our lifestyle.
I'll sit at a drive thru. 
I'll sit there behind fifteen other cars instead of getting up to make the eight foot walk to the totally empty counter.
Everything is mega meal, super sized. Want biggie fries, super sized, want to go large. 
You want to have thirty burgers for a nickel you fat mother fucker. There's room in the back. Take it!
Want a 55 gallon drum of Coke with that? It's only three more cents.

Sometimes you have to suffer a little bit in your youth to motivate yourself to succeed in later life.
Do you think if Bill Gates got laid in high school, do you think there'd be a Microsoft?
Of course not.
You got to spend a long time in your own locker with your underwear shoved up your ass before you start to think,
"You'll see. I'm going to take of the world of computers! I'll show them."

We're in one of the richest countries in the world,
but the minimum wage is lower than it was thirty five years ago.
There are homeless people everywhere.
This homeless guy asked me for money the other day.
I was about to give it to him and then I thought he was going to use it on drugs or alcohol.
And then I thought, that's what I'm going to use it on.
Why am I judging this poor bastard.
People love to judge homeless guys. Like if you give them money they're just going to waste it.
Well, he lives in a box, what do you want him to do? Save it up and buy a wall unit?
Take a little run to the store for a throw rug and a CD rack? He's homeless.
I walked behind this guy the other day. 
A homeless guy asked him for money.
He looks right at the homeless guy and says why don't you go get a job you bum.
People always say that to homeless guys like it is so easy.
This homeless guy was wearing his underwear outside his pants.
Outside his pants. I'm guessing his resume isn't all up to date.
I'm predicting some problems during the interview process.
I'm pretty sure even McDonalds has a "underwear goes inside the pants" policy.
Not that they enforce it really strictly, but technically I'm sure it is on the
i am in a terrible mood right now... absolutely terrible. i am cranky as hell, i feel fat, i have the worst allergies in the world, and i am stressed out! i will write more tomorrow.
i have allergies plus the flu... aaahhh!

I may have just made the dumbest decision... 

I dropped my classes because I am way too stressed. When my parents find out they are going to be so angry. My reasoning behind dropping my classes is simple - I feel that if I do not get my shit together then I will not succeed in school. I am so stressed and that is affecting my school work. I do not want to get C's in college, I would like to get A's. I cannot be accepted to Nursing school with bad grades. =/
I am not financially stable at all and that is putting an extremely large amount of stress on me. I literally lose sleep because my nights are spent laying in bed worrying about everything. I used ot be extremely immature and irresponsible with my money and I spent every cent. I have matured now and I know that I want to save but I am so far behind that I feel I will never catch up and get to the point where I can start saving again. 

$225 phone bill
$230 express card
$500 visa card
$400 mastercard
$500 that i owe to my grandma
$225 car payment 
$150 to parents
$200 car insurance
and now about $900 to fix my car

There is no way I can go to school full-time and work enough to get all of this paid off. So the only logical thing for me to do is take a break from school, get a second job, and get all of my bills paid for. Then I will go back to school and work very hard, get A's, get my Nursing degree, and begin my career. 

I feel absolutely horrible right now but I have to do this so I can regain control of my finances... and regain control of my life. I have never been this stressed out.  

I need to calm down before I have an anxiety attack... or a heart attack.

saturday was fun because i spent the day with jenny running errands, getting cute shoes, getting her hair done, etc. saturday night sucked. we felt completely invisible, it took forever to get a drink and some food, and then i got really sick and had to go home because i had taco bell earlier in the day that effed up my stomach. sunday sucked... my car overheated twice and nathan had to get it towed for me. it is in his dad's shop now getting worked on and so far my bill is at $350. i hate my car. i hate jeremiah for ruining my car. i dyed my hair and messed it up so nathan took me to get it fixed. he is such a sweetie and he has really been there for me a lot. we have been hanging out much more and things are going really well. we are not "official" or whatever but i think we should be. last night i went to nathans and we had a pizza and watched some tv. i drank an entire bottle of wine and stayed up entirely too late. i had to be at work at 4am and i was exhausted all day. i came home and took a nap and when i woke up, i was groggy and super grumpy. instead of going to class, i somewhat cleaned the house and did some laundry. i hate living here. my brother is such a pig and living with him stresses me out so much. i really want to take a break from school and get a second job and just pay off all of my bills/debts and move out. then when i go back to school, i will not be all stressed like i am right now. i have sooo much stress and i have been really moody lately. i need a break from it all, i really do. school, work, bills, car problems, living with my brother... it is all driving me absolutely crazy. atleast i found a sweet boy who treats me like a princess... that makes me happy. i am going to sleep. i have a really long day ahead of me tomorrow... =/ wake up at 4am, work from 6-2:30, study, classes from 4:30-8:30
it has been so long since jenny and i have gone out. tonight is going to be insane! <3 we are about to run some errands before tonights festivities. so excited!

i had a good day today. jenny and i got our pictures developed and they are great. some of them were form my trip to mississippi to see warren! i did not remember taking them! 
we went to get our nails done and they look pretty! i am not going out tonight. i am going to watch a few episodes of the dvd chris let me borrow (curb your enthusiasm) and then i am going to sleep. i plan to sleep in tomorrow, clean the house, finish my laundry, then go out tomorrow night. 
i wish i had more money right now because my room is totally plain. i wish i could buy decorations for my room such as vanilla candles, black and white pics for the walls, black blinds, a queen size down comforter, black silk sheets, and a bookshelf. i need a second job!!!
nathan and i fought today and it is so weird because we have only known each other for a week. i do not know what to think of things right now. i do like him though. he treats me like a princess and spoils me and i am not used to that at all - it is so nice. i need time to think... i think he does as well. 
tomorrow night jenny and i are going to downtown norfolk and we hope to get really, extremely, super, duper drunk. we are going to find a ride out there and set up a ride to pick us up so we do not have to worry about staying sober. we are so excited! <3
warren and i talked more this evening. there is a homeless dog in iraq that he is taking care of. he sent me pictures and it makes me sad - i wish he could bring her back because she is so cute. some american soldiers ran over her mom and brother with a truck for no reason... that is sick. warren told everyone that they would get killed if they touched the dog that he is taking care of. he put a flea collar on her, he feeds her, and plays with her daily. he has such a big heart. 

i miss warren. :(

i want to write to let off some steam but, honestly, i do not even know what to write. i hate repeating myself to people. when i tell you something, do not ask me over and over and over about it. it is annoying. i am annoyed. i cannot be with someone who is going to be worrysome. i cannot deal with that. ugghh... warren just logged online and he has not logged online in a long time. thank God because i really needed someone to talk to. i was heated earlier when i started this entry but now i am feeling better. he said he is my protector - he is right. sometimes i hate him but most of the time, i love him. i miss my best friend beeb. i miss kristin too. damn it. =/ i am so irritated and this is a shizzy feeling.

Kristin finally had her baby... Alexus Lynn King! Brandon's sending me pics of her tonight... I am so excited to see her! They said she's absolutely perfect! <3 This is a much-anticipated weekend because it is time for yet another girls night out! Jenny and I have not hung out in weeks and we are going through girls night out withdrawals. When she gets off of work tomorrow we are going to get our nails done and then we are going to get our pictures developed from previous crazy weekends. Saturday night we are going to our usual spots ~ Waterside and Granby Street! Yessss!!! I have been lazy all day and I have not gotten anything done. =/ I am working on some laundry but that is about it. I am about to get in the shower because I have no energy right now. Maybe that will give me some energy. There are so many things I want right now... queen size down comforter new sheets (black silk) black blinds in my room new clothes a digital camera new shoes black and white artsy posters for my room cool vanilla candles a bedroom set for my room and I want to get my nails done. Is that too much to ask? Bahaha... I really need a second job. I found one that would be perfect but the hours are from 4:30-8:30 daily and I cannot do that due to my school schedule. Grrr...

The family meeting was not as bad as I thought but I was told that I have to pay rent now. Damn it. I do not make enough money to pay all of my bills, plus pay back my mom the money I owe her, plus pay rent SOOO I need a second job. AHH!
Tomorrow I am going job hunting. I need a job that I could work 1:30pm - 5:30pm daily. What kind of job has those hours? McDonalds? I have no clue. 
I am cleaning up and doing laundry then I am spending time with Nathan. :)

What the fuck just happened? I just slept away almost 18 hours of my life... maybe my body is trying to tell me to slow down. I was supposed to go out with Jenny last night and I was really, really looking forward to going out. I came home and decided to take a nap at two in the afternoon. Next thing I know I am waking up at 10:30pm all confused and shit. I called Jenny and not two minutes after I got off the phone with her, I was passed out again. I woke up around 8 this morning and I feel weird. I usually do not even get 18 hours combined in a week, so 18 in one night is a little overwhelming. My dad called and he wants a "family meeting"... damn it. Basically, my brother and I will go over there and my parents will bitch at us about how we are doing everything wrong and how spoiled and unappreciative we are, when in reality it is my brother who is unappreciative, lazy, messy, etc. and I always get blamed. It is so ridiculous. It is days like this that I wish I could just go join the airforce and run away. Or maybe I am just fearing the worst and they're actually just going to see how we're doing. I know what I am getting in trouble for... money. They're going to tell me I owe them money for everything they've done for me lately - fixed my car, paid bills, etc. Fuck it. I'm going to their house with it all planned out to show them how much I make per paycheck and how I will pay them. I think showing up organized and prepared for the meeting will make me look better. Plus, if they start to gang up on me, I'll tell them my brother dropped all of his classes this semester. Bahahahaha... J/K... I'm not that big of a bitch, or am I? Naahhh... I am nervous because I always fuck things up and my parents know it and they always point out what I do wrong. But lately I have not done anything wrong. I have busted my ass in school and work... so I am curious to see what they will find wrong in me this time. I just have to hide my tongue ring because that shit will piss them off. They'll start with the, "That is so trashy and there you go spending your money on a piercing and blah blah blah." Honestly, I got it pierced because that shit makes me happy and right now with all of the stress I am going through, I deserve to do something every once and awhile that makes me happy. Geez. Wish me luck.

Chris and I went to get a smoothie and see a movie yesterday. I really do not like going to the movies unless it is with a group of friends and we are being goofy. I just get bored sitting there if it is just with one person.. especially if the movie does not interest me. We saw Man of the House... it was okay, I guess. I got bored. =/
Later, I hung out with Nathan and I had much more fun. We went to spy on someone for his friend who thinks her boyfriend is cheating on her. Sure enough, he was and we caught it. Haha. Then we went to Starbucks and got some coffee, then we ordered some pizza hut pizza, and went to his house to watch a movie. He kissed me and it felt nice. I have a crush on him and it is exciting because I think my parents will like him. I have the tendancy to date guys that my parents would not like - I will not go into detail with that but Jenny knows what I am talking about. ;) Shhh... 
But anyway, he is a cool guy and I am curious to see where this goes. 
I have to tell a few people that I have a crush on someone and they are not going to be happy but it is not fair to lead someone on. I have to tell "K" and I have to tell Chris... damn. 
I have two exams today and I am not prepared. Fuckkkk thank God next week is Spring Break because I need some time to get my shit together. 
I am going to study... or create a tiny cheat sheet, one of the two. :)

While I was at work yesterday, a guy approached me and slipped me a note with his phone number on it. He later came over to talk to me and he was totally awesome. So we decided to hang out when I got off work yesterday and we went to Finders Keepers and I got my tongue repierced (for the 4th time). He got his ear pierced (an industrial) and his face turned yellow and he almost puked. It looks good on him though. Afterwards, we went to a few places to get some applications (Nancy's Nook and the station) and then we went to his house and played old-school nintendo. I had a really great time hanging out with him and we're going to hang out again either today or tomorrow. We're going to fly a kite - how freakin' cute. 
Right now I'm about to meet up with Chris and go get a smoothie. I have class tonight at 7. Tomorrow I have the day off and I have to study, study, study... I have two exams tomorrow night. Fuck. 
I am in the worst mood right now. Grumpy as hell and I really do not know why. I suffer from the worst mood swings everrrr. Fuck, I am so tired right now. I need some sleep... or a drink or something. ;)
Jenny and I are going out Friday night. Yesssss!

bah... saturday night was pretty crazy. i almost took ecstacy but i decided not to. it would have been my first time rollin'. i took many shots of jager, drank many, many beers, went to the wave with some girls, danced like crazy, danced on stage, hardcore made out with a chick, drank even more, puked in another chicks car forcing her to pull over on the hampton roads bridge tunnel for me to puke some more, puked even more when i got back to her house, passed out drunk, and woke up at 8am when i was supposed to be at work at 6am. i had to call into work and tell them i was ill. fuck. it was super cool puking over the bridge into the water though. i was hungover all day and that night i went and had mexican food with my parents - big mistake. i puked some more. i worked sunday morning and then sunday evening i was lazy. i had work again today and my throat has been hurting. i think it is from throwing up... i really hope i am not getting sick. geez. jenny came over today and we watched some sex. bahaha. we watched the tommy lee and pamela anderson sex tape and it was so lame. she is very camera shy and kept covering up. jenny and i both agree that fake breasts are ugly. she looks like she has two giant melons glued to her. gross. and tommy lee was hairy. when he was not aroused his penis was very small and floppy but his shit got real big! as for the paris video, i was a little more interested in that one because i wanted to see her body. i am obsessed with skinny people and i wish i had her body - she is a damn twig. bones are hott. and as for rick soloman, his penis is very crooked, it looks like a damn rainbow or something. it was huge too, i would be so scared of that shiz. ouchie eew. i am skipping class tonight so i can study for thursdays anatomy lab exam. i also want to get to bed early because i have to wake up at 2:30am for work. damn, that's so super early. i dropped out of my statistics class because i could not handle the load. damn it. warren has been on my mind a lot more lately. he just logged online right when i typed his name - how effin' weird. =/ a sign, maybe? *sigh* i dyed my hair and the ends are darker. gooossshhhh. i am going to dye it again tomorrow - i hope it does not fall out. i am extremely lonely. casual sex is definately not what i want. i am craving passion, romance... and love. yes, i want a boyfriend. :(

-I woke up at 3:30am. +I'm not tired. +I'm feeling a little better. +My voice is back. -I cannot stop sneezing. -I have a runny/stuffy nose. +I look nice today. -I have to work. +I got car insurance for only $200 per month, which is good for my aweful driving record. -I still speed. -I haven't been eating healthy. -I feel fat. +Soon I'll be going running daily with my friend Scott. +My secret crush returns from LA today! <3 +My secret crush sent me a text message last night wishing me a Happy Valentine's Day! +I think this Dayquil is working. +Class is cancelled for tonight! -I have to write a research paper about Anthrax and it's due Thursday. -I have to memorize every bone in the body by Thursday for Anatomy Lab and I haven't started! -Warren sent me three dozen long stem roses, a small teddy bear, and a balloon. +Jenny's feeling better. +We'll probably go out this weekend... Girls Night Out! <3 -I recently contracted a virus on my computer from Kekai Boys music website. Damn it. +My dad installed Norton AntiVirus so I can kick the virus's ass. -My car is filthy. +I'm hanging out with my friend Chris on Friday night. -My nails look aweful due to lifting boxes and work. -Bert's heat lamp broke. -My room is messy. -I have to do laundry. -I am completely lost in my lost in my Statistics class. -I do not get paid enough. +People at work think I'm pretty.

unbelievable. warren is hundreds and hundreds of miles away in iraq and he still bugs the shit out of me. i put up an away message saying something along the lines that usher is sexy, and he freaks out. i hate him. hate is a strong word, but i've been putting up with his nonsense for five years and i am so tired of it. i need to completely cut off communication with him. he annoys me!!!

I watched Napoleon Dynamite and it was hilarious... then I watched the best movie everrrr. The Notebook. <3
I'm still sick and now I have Statistics at 9am on Saturday morning. Gross.

So it turns out that I'm not the only one that has crazy, random dreams. A girl I do not even know had this dream about me and it made me laugh when she told me about it. She seems really cool. This is what she wrote me... Heya, What's been going on? Not a whole lot around here. I just woke up really really confused. I just had a dream about you. lol Basically I drove all the way up there and I had friends with me and we basically just kinda sat around. Then you sat on my lap and I said that's probably not a good idea and you got upset and stormed away. Next thing I know there were people all over the place. You got lost in a crowd. Isn't that frickin' WEIRD? I don't talk to you all the time to be having dreams about you. lol I don't get it but ya, I thought I'd share with you. =) Have a good weekend! Anyway, I woke up this morning feeling pretty crappy but I still drove to work. When I got there, one of my coworkers said, "Giirrrlll, you be lookin' rough dis mornin'!" Haha. So I told her I didn't feel well and then my boss came up and saw how bad I looked and how bad I sounded when I was talking so he told me to go home and sleep. So I drove to Walmart and got some herbal tea, some honey, and some nyquil, then I went to Chickfila and got some breakfast. I ate, took some nyquil, and passed out. It's now almost 11 and I just had the most amazing nap everrrr. Now I remember why I absolutely LOVE nyquil and why I took it every single night last semester! LOL.
